gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Lakers 128, Bucks 124
gameRecap.excerpt: Anthony Davis (34 points, 23 rebounds, four blocks), Austin Reaves (29 points, season-high 14 rebounds, 10 assists) and DAngelo Russell (29 points, seven rebounds, 12 assists) combine for 92 points to lead the Lakers from a 19 point deficit, rally back and defeat the Bucks, 128-124 in 2OT.  Giannis Antetokounmpo (29 points, 21 rebounds, 11 assists) and Damian Lillard (27 points, five rebounds, eight assists) tally 56 for the Bucks in the losing effort.  The Lakers win their fourth consecutive game and improve to 40-32 on the season, while the Bucks fall to 46-26.
